Category.Name: SequenceControl
Category.ToolTip: Contains parameters to control the sequencer.
Category.Description: Contains parameters to control the sequencer, e.g. enabling/disabling the sequencer, establishing individual sequence sets, storing and loading them, defining the mode to advance from one set to the next, and setting the source to control the advance.

Boolean.Name: SequenceEnable
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables the sequencer.
Boolean.Description: Enables the sequencer.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceConfigurationMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets whether the sequencer can be configured.
Enumeration.Description: Sets whether the sequencer can be configured.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequencer can not be configured.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequencer can not be configured. The sequencer can now be used for image acquisition (by enabling SequenceEnable).

EnumEntry.Name: On
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequencer can be configured.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequencer can be configured. SequencerMode must be set to Off before setting this parameter to On.

Command.Name: SequenceAsyncRestart
Command.ToolTip: Allows asynchronous restart of the sequence of sequence sets.
Command.Description: Allows to restart the sequence of sequence sets, starting with the sequence set that has the lowest index number. The restart is asynchronous to the camera's frame trigger. Only available in Auto and Controlled sequence advance mode.

Command.Name: SequenceAsyncAdvance
Command.ToolTip: Allows asynchronous advance from one sequence set to the next one.
Command.Description: Allows to advance from the current sequence set to the next one. The advance is asynchronous to the camera's frame trigger. Only available in Controlled sequence advance mode.

Integer.Name: SequenceCurrentSet
Integer.ToolTip: Current sequence set.
Integer.Description: Current sequence set.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetTotalNumber
Integer.ToolTip: Total number of sequence sets in the sequence.
Integer.Description: Total number of sequence sets in the sequence.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetIndex
Integer.ToolTip: Index number of a sequence set.
Integer.Description: Index number of a sequence set.

Command.Name: SequenceSetLoad
Command.ToolTip: Loads a sequence set.
Command.Description: Loads an existing sequence set to make it the current sequence set.

Command.Name: SequenceSetStore
Command.ToolTip: Stores the current sequence set.
Command.Description: Stores the current sequence set. Storing the current sequence set will overwrite any already existing sequence set bearing the same index number. The sequence set is stored in the volatile memory and will therefore be lost if the camera is reset or if power is switched off.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetExecutions
Integer.ToolTip: Number of sequence set executions.
Integer.Description: Number of consecutive executions per sequence cycle for the selected sequence set. Only available in auto sequence advance mode.

Category.Name: SequenceControlConfiguration
Category.ToolTip: Contains parameters to configure the sequence set advance.
Category.Description: Contains parameters to configure the sequence set advance, e.g. selecting a sequence advance mode, selecting the source for controlling advance, and performing the related settings.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceAdvanceMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the sequence set advance mode.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the sequence set advance mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Auto
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The automatic sequence set advance mode is set.
EnumEntry.Description: The automatic sequence set advance mode is set. In this mode, the advance from one sequence set to the next occurs automatically as frame triggers are received.

EnumEntry.Name: Controlled
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The controlled sequence set advance mode is set.
EnumEntry.Description: The controlled sequence set advance mode is set. In this mode, the advance from one sequence set to the next proceeds in ascending sequence set index numbers according to the selected sequence control source (see the SequenceControlSource parameter).

EnumEntry.Name: FreeSelection
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The free selection sequence set advance mode is set.
EnumEntry.Description: The free selection sequence set advance mode is set. In this mode, the advance form one sequence set to the next as frame start triggers are received does not adhere to a specific preset sequence. The sequence sets can be selected at will using the states of an input line: The states of the input line set the sequence set addresses. These correspond to the sequence set index numbers and accordingly, the related sequence set is selected. For more information, see the SequenceAddressBitSelector and the SequenceAddressBitSource parameter documentation.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceControlSelector
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets whether the sequence control source should be set for sequence advance or for sequence restart.
Enumeration.Description: Sets whether the sequence control source should be set for sequence advance or for sequence restart. Once this value has been set, a control source must be chosen using the SequenceControlSource parameter.

EnumEntry.Name: Restart
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequence control source can be set for sequence set restart.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequence control source can be set for sequence set restart.

EnumEntry.Name: Advance
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequence control source can be set for sequence set advance.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequence control source can be set for sequence set advance. Only available in controlled sequence advance mode.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceControlSource

Enumeration.Description: Sets the source for sequence control.

EnumEntry.Name: Disabled
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Advance via asynchronous advance only.
EnumEntry.Description: Advance via asynchronous advance only.

Enumeration.Name: DemosaicingMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the demosaicing mode.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the demosaicing mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Simple
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Demosaicing is performed using a simple demosaicing algorithm.
EnumEntry.Description: Demosaicing is performed using a simple demosaicing algorithm. The Sharpness Enhancement and Noise Reduction features are disabled.

EnumEntry.Name: BaslerPGI
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Demosaicing is performed using the Basler PGI algorithm.
EnumEntry.Description: Demosaicing is performed using the Basler PGI algorithm. This algorithm uses advanced demosaicing methods. The Sharpness Enhancement and Noise Reduction features are enabled.

EnumEntry.Description: Basler PGI image optimizations are enabled.

Float.Name: NoiseReductionAbs
Float.ToolTip: Amount of noise reduction to apply.
Float.Description: Amount of noise reduction to apply. The higher the value, the less chroma noise will be visible in your images. However, too high values may result in image information loss. To enable this feature, the DemosaicingMode parameter must be set to BaslerPGI.

Integer.Name: NoiseReductionRaw
Integer.ToolTip: Amount of noise reduction to apply.
Integer.Description: Amount of noise reduction to apply. The higher the value, the less chroma noise will be visible in your images. However, too high values may result in image information loss. To enable this feature, the DemosaicingMode parameter must be set to BaslerPGI.

Float.Name: SharpnessEnhancementAbs
Float.ToolTip: Amount of sharpening to apply.
Float.Description: Amount of sharpening to apply. The higher the sharpness, the more distinct the image subject's contours will be. However, too high values may result in image information loss. To enable this feature, the DemosaicingMode parameter must be set to BaslerPGI.

If both binary numbers have at least one common bit set to 1 (i.e. the result of the And operation is non-zero), the corresponding camera belongs to the sub-group.

Enumeration.Name: FileOperationSelector
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the target operation for the currently selected file.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the target operation for the currently selected file. After an operation has been selected, the operation can be executed using the FileOperationExecute command.

EnumEntry.Name: Open
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The currently selected file can be opened.
EnumEntry.Description: The currently selected file can be opened. The access mode in which the file is opened can be set using the FileOpenMode parameter.

EnumEntry.Name: Close
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The currently selected file can be closed.
EnumEntry.Description: The currently selected file can be closed.

EnumEntry.Name: Read
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The currently selected file can be read.
EnumEntry.Description: The currently selected file can be read. When the FileOperationExecute command is executed, the camera reads FileAccessLength bytes from the device storage at the file relative offset FileAccessOffset into FileAccessBuffer.

EnumEntry.Name: Write
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The currently selected file can be written.
EnumEntry.Description: The currently selected file can be written. When the FileOperationExecute command is executed, the camera writes FileAccessLength bytes taken from the FileAccessBuffer into the device storage at the file relative offset FileAccessOffset.

Enumeration.Name: FileOpenMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the access mode in which a file is opened in the device.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the access mode in which a file is opened in the device.

EnumEntry.Name: Read
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Files are opened in read-only mode.
EnumEntry.Description: Files are opened in read-only mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Write
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Files are opened in write-only mode.
EnumEntry.Description: Files are opened in write-only mode.

Integer.Name: FileAccessOffset
Integer.ToolTip: File access offset.
Integer.Description: File access offset. Controls the mapping between the device file storage and the FileAccessBuffer.

Integer.Name: FileAccessLength
Integer.ToolTip: File access length.
Integer.Description: File access length. Controls the mapping between the device file storage and the FileAccessBuffer.

Enumeration.Name: FileOperationStatus
Enumeration.ToolTip: Returns the file operation execution status.
Enumeration.Description: Returns the file operation execution status.

EnumEntry.Name: Success
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The file operation was successful.
EnumEntry.Description: The file operation was successful.

EnumEntry.Name: Failure
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The file operation has failed.
EnumEntry.Description: The file operation has failed.

Integer.Name: FileOperationResult
Integer.ToolTip: File operation result.
Integer.Description: File operation result. For read or write operations, the number of successfully read/written bytes is returned.

Integer.Name: FileSize
Integer.ToolTip: Size of the currently selected file in bytes.
Integer.Description: Size of the currently selected file in bytes.

Command.Name: FileOperationExecute
Command.ToolTip: Executes the operation selected by FileOperationSelector.
Command.Description: Executes the operation selected by FileOperationSelector on the selected file.
